<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98374540338730></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98374540338730><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/search.shtml?id=3443&mid=98374540338730 style='color: darkblue;'>Paladins</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Mar 4th 5:36 PM</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>For a Paladin, these things are easy as pie.  Sometimes I can even solo a hag--provided that my dex is buffed.  All you've got to do is have a Ghoulbane (Belay the whole "Not everyone has a GB!" schlop, because I'll give ya a way to do it without.  =)  Anyways, if you've got a GB, and you've got about 100 Dex, all you've got to do is hammer away on her.  Keep LoH charged just in case, and equip a good sheild--my favorite is the Crested Mistmoore Sheild for it's +Dex.  If you're Level 30 and up looking for some easy EXP or her gossimer, then keep her stunned and bash away.  Otherwise, just keep bashing whenever she begins to cast.  You'll need to do it very quickly as her force Strike spell is pretty quickly fired off.<br><br>Use the normal undead routine, Ward Undead, hammer away.  Dismiss should proc about every four hits, and since they've only got like 600 HP, she should drop fast.<br><br>If you don't have a GB, then your chances of soloing one are very slim.  You'll need at least a Level 24 Cleric, because her DD is about 300.  But, if you've got like a Wurmslayer, then.. well.. you're gonna kill her in like ten seconds anyways.  =)<br><br>Enjoy, folks.<br><br>Melious Soulblaze, Paladin of the everbroken Morell-Thule.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
